        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 7 at 1:47PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 147 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms capable of producing microbursts extending from 15
miles north of Simla to 5 miles southwest of Elbert, or extending
from 26 miles west of Limon to 43 miles southeast of Denver, moving
southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Elbert, Simla, Matheson and Fondis.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
